The paper deals with the task of image captioning, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes two different models for injecting sentiments into image captions, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed models, which involves metrics and analysis, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category.
